section2.body:
ORUS Gallery may collect personal data voluntarily provided by users, including:
• name;
• email address;
• message content;
• professional or institutional affiliation, when provided;
• communication preferences;
• any information submitted through the contact form or by email.
The website may also collect limited technical data, such as browsing information, device type, browser type, language preferences and anonymous usage data, where applicable.

section3.body:
Personal data may be used for the following purposes:
• responding to enquiries sent through the website or by email;
• managing communication with collectors, artists, institutions, press representatives and other professional contacts;
• providing information about exhibitions, artists, projects or gallery activities, when requested;
• improving the website and user experience;
• ensuring the security, maintenance and proper functioning of the website;
• complying with legal or regulatory obligations where applicable.
ORUS Gallery does not sell personal data.

section4.body:
Personal data is processed only where there is a lawful basis to do so, including:
• the user's consent, when information is submitted voluntarily;
• the legitimate interest of ORUS Gallery in responding to enquiries and managing professional relationships;
• compliance with legal obligations where applicable.

section10.body:
In accordance with applicable data protection regulations, including the GDPR where applicable, users may have the right to:
• access their personal data;
• request correction of inaccurate data;
• request deletion of their data;
• object to certain processing;
• request restriction of processing;
• request data portability, where applicable;
• withdraw consent at any time, where processing is based on consent.
To exercise these rights, users may contact: contact@orusgallery.com
Users also have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent data protection authority.

section4.body:
Users agree to use the website lawfully and respectfully.
It is strictly prohibited to:
• use the website for unlawful, fraudulent or harmful purposes;
• attempt to interfere with the proper functioning or security of the website;
• use automated systems, bots, scraping tools or data extraction methods without authorization;
• copy, extract or reuse website content without permission;
• upload, transmit or submit any harmful, offensive, misleading or unlawful content;
• attempt to gain unauthorized access to the website, servers or related systems.
ORUS Gallery reserves the right to take any appropriate action in the event of misuse of the website.

section8.body:
ORUS Gallery makes reasonable efforts to maintain access to the website and ensure the accuracy of its content.
However, ORUS Gallery does not guarantee that the website will be uninterrupted, error-free, secure or permanently available.
ORUS Gallery shall not be held liable for any direct or indirect damage resulting from:
• access to or use of the website;
• temporary unavailability of the website;
• inaccuracies, omissions or errors in the information displayed;
• technical issues, viruses, bugs or security incidents;
• use of external links or third-party services.
Users remain responsible for their own use of the website and for taking appropriate measures to protect their devices and data.
